
  <sn><md>### Percentage Increase or Decrease in Value {.text-center}

**Key Formulas**

* **If a value of x increases by y%, the new value is:**
  $$
  (100 + y)\% \text{ of } x
  $$

* **If a value of x decreases by y%, the new value is:**
  $$
  (100 - y)\% \text{ of } x
  $$
* **Final Equation** :
  $$
   \text{Past Value} = \frac{\text{Current Value} \times 100}{\text{corresponding past percentage of current value}}
  $$
   $$
   \text{x} = \frac{\text{Current Value} \times 100}{100 \pm y}
   $$
**Important Concept**

**100% always represents the original or complete value.**<br>
When a value increases or decreases, the resulting value represents a percentage of the original/previous value.
</md></sn>
