**58. If a country's population doubled every 10 years from 1970 to 2010, what was the percentage increase during that period? [NSI Junior Field Officer - 2019]**<br>
a. 300\%<br> b. `700\%`<br> c. 800\%<br> d. 1000\%

+++ check

Let the population in 1970 be $x$.

```text
1970    1980    1990    2000    2010
 x       2x      4x      8x      16x
```

Increase:

$$
16x - x = 15x
$$

Percentage increase:

$$
\frac{15x}{x} \times 100 = 1500\%
$$

**Answer: 1500\%**

⚠️ The answer given in the source (700\%) assumes doubling only up to the year 2000 ($x \to 8x$). Since 1970 to 2010 covers four 10-year intervals, the mathematically correct increase is **1500\%**.
+++
